explanation: The solution uses a sliding window approach to track the maximum consecutive count of a target character ('T' or 'F') that can be achieved by changing at most k characters. It maintains a window defined by left and right pointers, expanding the window to the right and shrinking it from the left when the number of changes needed exceeds k. This approach efficiently computes the maximum consecutive count in a single pass through the string.

